<!-- Quiz 1: Basic Reinforcement vs Punishment, Question 1 -->
<MarkupProblem id="reinforce_punish_practice_1" title="Question 1: Sticker" showanswer="never"><![CDATA[
## Practice Quiz: Reinforcement vs. Punishment

>>Liam reads a book every night because he earns a sticker for each completed book.<<

(x) Reinforcement {{ Correct }}
( ) Punishment    {{ Try Again }}

[explanation]
Getting the sticker increases the likelihood that Liam will read the book, so this is reinforcement.
[/explanation]
]]></MarkupProblem>

<!-- Quiz 1: Basic Reinforcement vs Punishment, Question 2 -->
<MarkupProblem id="reinforce_punish_practice_1b" title="Question 2: Asking" showanswer="never"><![CDATA[
## Practice Quiz: Reinforcement vs. Punishment

>>Daniel puts away his toys so his parents will stop asking him to clean up.<<

(x) Reinforcement {{ Correct }}
( ) Punishment    {{ Try Again }}

[explanation]
The parent's asking increases the likelihood that Daniel will put his toys away, so this is reinforcement.
[/explanation]
]]></MarkupProblem>

<!-- Quiz 1: Basic Reinforcement vs Punishment, Question 3 -->
<MarkupProblem id="reinforce_punish_practice_1c" title="Question 3: Getting Burned" showanswer="never"><![CDATA[
## Practice Quiz: Reinforcement vs. Punishment

>>Lucas stops touching the hot stove after he accidentally burns his hand.<<

( ) Reinforcement {{ Try Again }}
(x) Punishment    {{ Correct }}

[explanation]
Getting his hand burned reduces the likelihood that Daniel will continue his previous behavior (touching the hot stove), so this is punishment.
[/explanation]
]]></MarkupProblem>

<!-- Quiz 1: Basic Reinforcement vs Punishment, Question 4 -->
<MarkupProblem id="reinforce_punish_practice_1d" title="Question 4: Tantrum" showanswer="never"><![CDATA[
## Practice Quiz: Reinforcement vs. Punishment

>>Victoria throws a tantrum at dinner to get out of eating her vegetables.<<

(x) Reinforcement {{ Correct }}
( ) Punishment    {{ Try Again }}

[explanation]
Getting out of eating her vegetables makes Victoria more likely to throw another tantrum, so this is reinforcement.
[/explanation]
]]></MarkupProblem>

<!-- Quiz 1: Basic Reinforcement vs Punishment, Question 5 -->
<MarkupProblem id="reinforce_punish_practice_1e" title="Question 5: Glaring" showanswer="never"><![CDATA[
