<!-- Quiz 2: Four Types of Operant Conditioning, Question 1 -->
<MarkupProblem id="four_types_practice_1" title="Question 1: Sticker" showanswer="never"><![CDATA[
## Practice Quiz: The Four Types of Operant Conditioning

>>Liam reads a book every night because he earns a sticker for each completed book.<<

(x) Positive Reinforcement {{ Correct }}
( ) Negative Reinforcement {{ Try Again }}
( ) Positive Punishment    {{ Try Again }}
( ) Negative Punishment    {{ Try Again }}

[explanation]
- Something desirable is added (stickers) - Positive
- Behavior happens more often (reading a book every night) - Reinforcement
[/explanation]
]]></MarkupProblem>

<!-- Quiz 2: Four Types of Operant Conditioning, Question 2 -->
<MarkupProblem id="four_types_practice_1b" title="Question 2: Asking" showanswer="never"><![CDATA[
## Practice Quiz: The Four Types of Operant Conditioning

>>Daniel puts away his toys so his parents will stop asking him to clean up.<<

( ) Positive Reinforcement {{ Try Again }}
(x) Negative Reinforcement {{ Correct }}
( ) Positive Punishment    {{ Try Again }}
( ) Negative Punishment    {{ Try Again }}

[explanation]
- Something undesirable is being taken away (parents asking him to clean up) - Negative
- Behavior happens more often (putting toys away) - Reinforcement
[/explanation]
]]></MarkupProblem>

